Pure Foods, RFM, San Miguel, SM: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-03-03T00:55:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/pure-foods-rfm-san-miguel-sm-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and prices are as of noon yesterday
in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.3 percent to
3,773.71.    RFM Corp. (RFM)  : The Philippine food and drinks company
said it will pay 2.97 centavos a share in cash dividends, a
stock exchange filing showed. The stock decreased 3 percent to
1.60 pesos.    San Miguel  Pure Foods Co. Inc. (PF PM): The hotdog-maker
will list 15 million preferred shares that it sold at 1,000
pesos each last month. Pure Foods was unchanged at 1,400 pesos
when it was last traded on Feb. 28.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  ,
parent of Pure Foods, fell 1.6 percent to 170.20 pesos.    SM Investments Corp. (SM)  : The owner of the largest
Philippine bank and biggest shopping mall operator said profit
rose 15 percent to 18.4 billion pesos ($307 million). The stock
fell 0.9 percent to 457 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  